  "summaries": [
    "The <b>Wizard</b> is a <linked>Hardmode</linked> <linked>NPC</linked> vendor who sells <linked>magic</linked>-related items. As soon as the <linked>Wall of Flesh</linked> has been defeated, he rarely spawns in the <linked>Cavern</linked> layer or below as the stationary <b>Bound Wizard</b>, and talking to him in this state will free him. If the Bound Wizard is killed, he will still be able to respawn afterwards; if the Wizard NPC is killed, he will move in again after some time as long as there are vacant <linked>houses</linked>.",
    "<span class=\"eico i1 i2 i4\" title=\"Desktop, Console and Mobile versions\"><b></b><i></i></span> When <linked>enemies</linked> are in his vicinity, the Wizard hurls fireballs at them in a similar fashion to the <linked>Flower of Fire</linked> while casting an aesthetic magic circle, dealing 18 / <linked>27</linked> / <linked>31</linked> damage.",
    "<span class=\"eico i1 i2 i4\" title=\"Desktop, Console and Mobile versions\"><b></b><i></i></span> He will occasionally replace his regular quote with a comment about the player's <linked>luck</linked>. This is the only way to estimate a player's luck value in the game.",
    "The Bound Wizard is one of the few entities that can be detected by the <span class=\"eil\"><span><linked>Lifeform Analyzer</linked></span><span class=\"eico s i1 i2 i4\" title=\"Desktop, Console and Mobile versions\"><b></b><i></i></span></span> or its upgrades."
